2026-04-06 01:29:54 - Agent_20260406012402 - INFO - [+] Agent signaled completion: Reviewed 7 queries covering OS command injection in Apache NiFi components. Key findings:

1. TRUE POSITIVES (2 confirmed):
   - ShellRunner (nifi-framework) at line 59: Uses ProcessBuilder(["sh", "-c", command]) with dynamically-built shell command strings from OS group data. Shell metacharacters in group names would be interpreted.
   - ShellRunner (nifi-registry) at line 59: Identical pattern - same shell injection risk.

2. TRUE POSITIVE - Argument Injection (1):
   - ScriptEventHookProvider: Event field values passed directly as process arguments without sanitization.

3. MANUAL REVIEW (2):
   - ExecuteProcess (line 225): FlowFile attributes evaluated via EL flow to ProcessBuilder args - by design but risky.
   - ExecuteStreamCommand (line 382): Same pattern as ExecuteProcess - EL-evaluated FlowFile attributes in command args.

4. FALSE POSITIVES (2):
   - Bootstrap getChildProcesses/killProcessTree in RunNiFi, RunMiNiFi, RunNiFiRegistry: Array-form exec with numeric PIDs from OS, no shell interpretation. CodeQL socket-to-command flow tracing is a false positive.

Total: 7 findings submitted (2 tp, 2 fp, 1 tp-argument-injection, 2 mr)
